fabric.worker

Class RemoteStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • fabric.net.RemoteNode<RemoteStore>
      • fabric.worker.RemoteStore
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Store, java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    InProcessStore

    public class RemoteStore
extends RemoteNode<RemoteStore>
implements Store, java.io.Serializable
    Encapsulates a Store. This class maintains two connections to the store (one with SSL, for worker requests; and one without, for dissemination requests) and manages all communication. Stores can only be obtained through the Worker.getStore() interface. For each remote store, there should be at most one RemoteStore object representing that store.

      • updateCache

        public void updateCache(SerializedObject update)
        Updates the worker's cache of objects that originate from this store. If an object with the given onum exists in cache, it is evicted and replaced with the given serialized object; any transactions using the object are aborted and retried. If the object does not exist in cache, then the cache is not updated.
